{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.opticalaberration.hummingbird\/tutorials\/Hummingbird\/Todos-4-Postgres"},"sections":[{"chapter":"Store Todos in a database","estimatedTimeInMinutes":15,"backgroundImage":"hummingbird.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Now we have a working API and a way to test it, lets look into storing our todos in a Postgres database with PostgresNIO.","type":"text"}]}],"title":"Use PostgresNIO to store your Todos in a Postgres database","image":"hummingbird.png","kind":"hero"},{"tasks":[{"contentSection":[{"media":"hummingbird.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Setup a Postgres database to use with the Todos application."}]}],"kind":"contentAndMedia","mediaPosition":"trailing"}],"title":"Setup your Postgres database","anchor":"Setup-your-Postgres-database","stepsSection":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You’ll need to install postgres on your system if you don’t already have it. Detailed instructions on installing Postgres can be found "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.postgresql.org\/download\/"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"code":"todos-postgres-01.sh","caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once you have installed Postgres follow the instructions on screen to start your Postgres database service."}]}],"type":"step","media":null,"runtimePreview":null},{"media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Postgres install comes with "},{"code":"psql","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" the commandline interface to Postgres. We are going to use this to create a new database and a new role."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":null,"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note the SQL commands all end in a semi-colon. The "},{"code":"\\c","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" command connects to a database and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\q"},{"type":"text","text":" command quits "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pqsl"},{"text":". You can find out more about ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"psql"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/www.postgresql.org\/docs\/current\/app-psql.html","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"todos-postgres-02.sh","type":"step"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We return to our project…"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"todos-postgres-03.swift","caption":[],"type":"step","runtimePreview":null,"media":null},{"runtimePreview":null,"caption":[],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"And add PostgresNIO as a dependency","type":"text"}]}],"media":null,"type":"step","code":"todos-postgres-04.swift"},{"runtimePreview":null,"code":"todos-postgres-05.swift","caption":[],"media":null,"type":"step","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Sources\/App\/Application+build.swift…"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"step","media":null,"code":"todos-postgres-06.swift","runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"we add a new requirement "},{"code":"inMemoryTesting","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to ","type":"text"},{"code":"AppArguments","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". This will decide whether we store Todos in memory or a Postgres database."}]}],"caption":[]},{"caption":[],"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step","media":null,"code":"todos-postgres-07.swift","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We then need to add implementations of this requirement in Sources\/App\/App.swift"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"runtimePreview":null,"caption":[],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"and Tests\/AppTests\/AppTests.swift","type":"text"}]}],"type":"step","code":"todos-postgres-08.swift","media":null},{"code":"todos-postgres-09.swift","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We are going to use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PostgresClient"},{"type":"text","text":" from PostgresNIO for our Postgres support. The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"inMemoryTesting"},{"type":"text","text":" flag is used to decide on whether we should set one up. Note the Postgres configuration details are the same as the Postgres role we set up earlier in psql."}]}],"runtimePreview":null,"media":null,"type":"step","caption":[]},{"media":null,"caption":[],"code":"todos-postgres-10.swift","type":"step","runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PostgresClient"},{"text":" sets up background processes that requires lifecycle management. You can add a service to ","type":"text"},{"code":"Application","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to have its lifecycle managed as long as it conforms to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Service"},{"type":"text","text":". This is done by adding it to an internally held "},{"code":"ServiceGroup","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". More details on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Service"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"ServiceGroup","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" can be found in the documentation for ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/swiftpackageindex.com\/swift-server\/swift-service-lifecycle\/main\/documentation\/servicelifecycle"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"contentSection":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Implement a version of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TodoRepository"},{"text":" that uses ","type":"text"},{"code":"PostgresClient","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":"hummingbird.png","mediaPosition":"trailing","kind":"contentAndMedia"}],"title":"Setup a Postgres repository","anchor":"Setup-a-Postgres-repository","stepsSection":[{"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We start our Postgres support by creating a type conforming to ","type":"text"},{"code":"TodoRepository","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" that uses "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PostgresClient"},{"type":"text","text":" from PostgresNIO. The functions are filled out with dummy code just now so the project will compile."}]}],"caption":[],"media":null,"code":"todos-postgres-11.swift"},{"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"I won’t go into any great detail about the SQL calls. That is not the purpose of this tutorial. We will cover how you construct, send calls and parse their results with "},{"code":"PostgresClient","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as we proceed through the tutorial."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":null,"media":null,"type":"step","code":"todos-postgres-12.swift","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If we are going to be saving our todos to a database we are going to need a table to store them in.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"step","media":null,"code":"todos-postgres-10.swift","runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Return to "},{"code":"buildApplication(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in Application+build.swift…"}]}],"caption":[]},{"caption":[],"type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use the newly created "},{"code":"TodoPostgresRepository","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and once the ","type":"text"},{"code":"PostgresClient","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is running call ","type":"text"},{"code":"createTable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"media":null,"code":"todos-postgres-14.swift","runtimePreview":null},{"code":"todos-postgres-23.swift","runtimePreview":null,"media":null,"caption":[],"type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Update "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"buildRouter(_:)"},{"text":" to take the repository as an argument and pass it to the controller.","type":"text"}]}]},{"media":null,"caption":[],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Back to TodoPostgresRepository.swift to start implementing our repository methods.","type":"text"}]}],"runtimePreview":null,"code":"todos-postgres-12.swift","type":"step"},{"type":"step","runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To run a SQL query call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PostgresClient.query(_:logger:)"},{"type":"text","text":" with the query string and a Logger`."}]}],"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Wait a sec! If you look closer that query looks like it’s got SQL injection. That’s a classic security issue. Except this isn’t the case here. The object being constructed is not a ","type":"text"},{"code":"String","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" but a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PostgresQuery"},{"text":" which uses ","type":"text"},{"code":"StringInterpolation","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to create parameter bindings for all the interpolated variables."}]}],"code":"todos-postgres-15.swift","media":null},{"media":null,"runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"get"},{"type":"text","text":" method demonstrates how you get data returned from a query. The query returns a sequence of rows. You extract the data from the row by decoding it as a tuple. In this case there should only be one row so we return immediately as soon as we have it."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","caption":[],"code":"todos-postgres-16.swift"},{"type":"step","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"list","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is very similar to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"get"},{"text":". Except there is no ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WHERE"},{"type":"text","text":" clause in the SQL and we return all of the rows returned from the query instead of just the first."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"code":"todos-postgres-17.swift","caption":[],"runtimePreview":null},{"code":"todos-postgres-18.swift","caption":[],"media":null,"runtimePreview":null,"type":"step","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"patch"},{"type":"text","text":" has a complication where we only want to include the non optional values in the "},{"code":"UPDATE","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" query otherwise we’ll be setting database columns to null. You could do this dynamically and build a "},{"code":"PostgresQuery.StringInterpolation","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" bit by bit but it is safer just to provide the full query strings for each situation.","type":"text"}]}]},{"media":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"And finally the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"delete"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"deleteAll"},{"type":"text","text":" functions. This completes the implementation of the Postgres todos repository."}]}],"caption":[],"code":"todos-postgres-20.swift","runtimePreview":null,"type":"step"},{"type":"step","code":"todos-postgres-21.swift","media":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you go to Tests\/AppTests\/AppTests.swift…"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"caption":[],"runtimePreview":null},{"media":null,"runtimePreview":null,"caption":[],"type":"step","code":"todos-postgres-22.swift","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can switch the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"inMemoryTesting"},{"type":"text","text":" boolean to false to test your Postgres solution."}]}]},{"caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The code for this tutorial can be found in the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/hummingbird-project\/hummingbird-examples\/tree\/main\